@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Knight" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To move the Knight, just click on the tile where you want it to
go. You must move the Knight the same way as you would do in the
chess game, that is, an "L" move (2 spaces horizontally and 1 space
vertically, or 1 space horizontally and 2 spaces vertically). If
the move is possible, the Knight will go there. When the Knight
leaves a tile, it disappears, so you cannot go back.

  The game ends when you get to the last tile or, if the Knight can
no longer move, the game will display the number of remaining tiles.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button or by pressing on the 'N' key.

NOTE: If your Workbench has 8 coulours or more, the colour of the
      Knight can be changed by clicking on it.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

